This reflecting telescope

00:29:37.470 --> 00:29:38.760
dates back to 1934.

00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:40.410
Its focal length...

00:29:41.520 --> 00:29:43.380
Let's go inside for a closer look.

00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:46.650
[Jin Zhao]

00:29:53.560 --> 00:29:54.880
When do you get off work?

00:29:54.880 --> 00:29:57.190
I'm showing some visitors around
the observatory.

00:29:57.190 --> 00:29:58.920
It'll be over in a little while.

00:29:59.520 --> 00:30:01.120
Then carry on with your work.

00:30:04.360 --> 00:30:04.990
Jiang Mu.

00:30:06.600 --> 00:30:07.950
They have other plans for tonight.

00:30:07.950 --> 00:30:10.410
We just need to see them off
to their vehicle.

00:30:10.740 --> 00:30:12.870
Want to have hot pot together tonight?

00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:14.350
I already have plans.

00:30:15.860 --> 00:30:16.660
Alright then.

00:30:17.330 --> 00:30:17.720
Let's go.

00:30:17.720 --> 00:30:18.250
Let's go.

00:30:24.040 --> 00:30:25.630
Listen, don't always
bury yourself in work.

00:30:25.630 --> 00:30:29.160
You're not getting any younger.
Consider finding a boyfriend.

00:30:31.520 --> 00:30:32.710
Why are you here?

00:30:34.710 --> 00:30:35.550
Didn't I tell you to wait for me

00:30:35.550 --> 00:30:38.550
-at the foot of the mountain?
-I wanted to come see you.

00:30:42.920 --> 00:30:44.180
How did you get up here?

00:30:45.050 --> 00:30:45.880
By cable car.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:52.460
Why are you making such a fuss
about him coming up the mountain?

00:30:53.710 --> 00:30:54.670
Who is this?

00:30:55.360 --> 00:30:56.470
My name is Gu Zhijie.

00:30:56.470 --> 00:30:57.630
I'm Jiang Mu's

00:30:57.910 --> 00:30:58.910
half-colleague?

00:31:02.280 --> 00:31:03.120
And this is?

00:31:03.390 --> 00:31:04.990
My ex-boyfriend of one week.

00:31:05.910 --> 00:31:07.370
I've heard a lot about you.

00:31:08.190 --> 00:31:09.950
What do you mean by "half-colleague"?

00:31:09.950 --> 00:31:11.280
I'm Jiang Mu's senior from school.

00:31:11.280 --> 00:31:12.560
Although we don't work together,

00:31:12.560 --> 00:31:15.020
I kind of tricked her into
coming to Nanjing.

00:31:15.120 --> 00:31:16.550
We're all in the same field,

00:31:16.550 --> 00:31:18.470
so we're half-colleagues.

00:31:22.060 --> 00:31:24.390
Qin and I will
see the leaders off tonight.

00:31:24.470 --> 00:31:26.560
You're really not
coming to dinner tonight?

00:31:26.560 --> 00:31:27.910
I'll call you later.

00:31:28.540 --> 00:31:29.090
Okay.

00:31:29.560 --> 00:31:31.020
Then I'll get back to work.

00:31:37.510 --> 00:31:38.510
Half-colleague.

00:31:41.540 --> 00:31:43.270
Is this your first time up here?

00:31:46.080 --> 00:31:47.480
Want me to give you a tour?

00:31:48.800 --> 00:31:50.330
If it's convenient for you.

00:31:50.600 --> 00:31:52.840
Convenient or not, you're already here.

00:31:52.840 --> 00:31:55.100
Wouldn't it be a waste not to look around?

00:31:56.430 --> 00:31:57.490
I already told you.

00:31:58.280 --> 00:31:59.480
I just came to see you.

00:32:01.150 --> 00:32:02.280
To see me?

00:32:03.430 --> 00:32:04.960
So, what have you observed?

00:32:10.560 --> 00:32:11.560
I came to see...

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:14.540
if I've scared you away again.

00:32:18.910 --> 00:32:20.800
And what's your conclusion?

00:32:32.520 --> 00:32:34.080
This celestial globe before us

00:32:34.080 --> 00:32:35.360
is cast in bronze

00:32:35.470 --> 00:32:36.520
and can rotate.

00:32:36.910 --> 00:32:38.330
It's about three chi in diameter

00:32:38.330 --> 00:32:39.190
and is embedded with

00:32:39.190 --> 00:32:41.080
1,449 bronze pins,

00:32:41.320 --> 00:32:42.520
representing the stars

00:32:42.520 --> 00:32:43.920
visible to the naked eye.

00:32:47.120 --> 00:32:47.910
Is this ring

00:32:48.190 --> 00:32:49.390
the meridian circle?

00:32:51.280 --> 00:32:52.320
That's right.

00:32:52.880 --> 00:32:55.230
Mr. Visitor, you know your astronomy.

00:32:57.370 --> 00:32:58.170
Just a little.

00:33:05.450 --> 00:33:06.710
This is a celestial globe,

00:33:06.710 --> 00:33:09.390
called Huntianyi or Hunxiang
in ancient times.

00:33:10.040 --> 00:33:11.080
Back in the Eastern Han Dynasty,

00:33:11.080 --> 00:33:12.230
there was a star-gazing boy

00:33:12.230 --> 00:33:14.090
named Zhang Heng who improved it,

00:33:14.090 --> 00:33:14.880
giving it the function

00:33:14.880 --> 00:33:17.410
of demonstrating celestial body movements.

00:33:17.990 --> 00:33:18.950
My work focuses on

00:33:18.950 --> 00:33:20.600
the dynamics of

00:33:20.600 --> 00:33:22.400
multi-body celestial systems.

00:33:24.120 --> 00:33:25.040
Come to think of it,

00:33:25.040 --> 00:33:28.220
you were actually the one
who first introduced me to all this.

00:33:28.220 --> 00:33:29.680
Have you been busy lately?

00:33:44.700 --> 00:33:46.100
Let me ask you something.

00:33:47.910 --> 00:33:49.320
If I really had a fiancé

00:33:49.600 --> 00:33:50.930
who loved playing games

00:33:51.120 --> 00:33:52.600
and chasing women,

00:33:53.020 --> 00:33:54.020
what would you do?

00:33:58.290 --> 00:33:59.490
Do you want the truth?

00:33:59.710 --> 00:34:00.390
Of course.

00:34:02.430 --> 00:34:03.890
I'd make you willingly...

00:34:05.420 --> 00:34:07.020
